    <title>Preferences - Interface</title>
    <p>
        The following image displays the Interface preferences dialog:
    </p>
    
    <figure>
        <desc>The Interface preferences dialog</desc>
        <media type="image" src="Images/preferences-interface.png"/>
    </figure>
    
    <p>This dialog offers the configuration of several interface related aspects.</p>
    
    <section id="settings">
        <title>Settings</title>
        <list>
            <title>Main:</title>
            <item><p>Hide on close - If you enable this option, GMPC's main window will be minimized instead of closed when requested. If the tray icon is shown, GMPC will hide it's main window.</p></item>
            <item><p>Stylize album covers - TODO</p></item>
            <item><p>Stop playing on exit - If this option is enabled, GMPC will stop playback before quitting.</p></item>
            <item><p>Show songlist tooltip - Enable this, if you want tooltips showing further information when hovering items in songlists.</p></item>
            <item><p>Show buttons instead of dropdown in collapsed view - When enabled, this will show buttons instead of a dropdown to switch between the different browsers in collapsed view.</p></item>
            <item><p>Enable search as you type. (Might be slow) - You don't have to press enter to search.</p></item>
        </list>
        
        <list>
            <title>Playlist:</title>
            <item><p>Center playing song - The currently playing song will be centered in the "Play Queue" browser by automatically scrolling the playlist when the song changes.</p></item>
            <item><p>Save position and size between sessions - TODO</p></item>
        </list>
    </section>

    <section id="advancedSettings">
        <title>Advanced settings</title>
        <p>When you click the "Advanced sttings" button, a window will appear giving you even further configuration options.</p>
        <list>
            <title>Interface</title>
            <item><p>Hide album art - This will hide the album art in the "Now Playing" browser and the notification popup.</p></item>
            <item><p>Hide favorite icon - This hides the favorite icon.</p></item>
            <item><p>Use backdrops (restart required) - TODO</p></item>
        </list>

        <list>
            <title>Browsers</title>
            <item><p>These items allow you to individually select, which of GMPC's internal browsers should be visible.</p></item>
        </list>
        
    </section>

</page>
